After examining your spec, choosing your libraries your pre-dev rituals, etc., when you sit down to write that first line; think 
hypothetically about your last line and ask yourself - "did you have a good code organization strategy?"


SugarSkull tries to address some of the following...

	A. Clarification of the execution path.
	B. Isolation of intention.
	C. Exclusion without interference.
	D. Static conditional execution.
	E. Fewest moving parts.